cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on distributed stream processing systems hosted on cloud data centers for real-time data processing and analytics.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the Internet of Things (IoT) and the use of sensors and actuators to monitor and manage physical, environmental, and human systems in real-time.
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper mentions data pre-processing, statistical summarization, and predictive analytics, which are common tasks in database systems.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the development of a benchmark suite for evaluating distributed stream processing systems for IoT applications.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the closed-loop responsiveness and decision making of IoT applications, which are related to control systems.
